{
    "word": "Baste",
    "definitions": [
        "To sprinkle flour and salt and drip butter or fat on, as on meat in roasting.",
        "To mark with tar, as sheep.",
        "To sew loosely, or with long stitches; -- usually, that the work may be held in position until sewed more firmly."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "One man was basted by the keeper for carrying some people over on his back through the waters."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. basten, OF. bastir, F. b, prob. fr. OHG. bestan to sew, MHG. besten to bind, fr. OHG. bast bast. See Bast.]"
}